db.collection_name.find().sort(<sort>) =>   {ascending = 1}  {descending = -1}

db.collection_name.find().toArray()  =>  converts the objects into an array of objects to access it by index.

db.collection_name.find().next()  =>  return the next document in a cursor

cursor.batchSize()  =>  to control the number of documents MongoDB will return to the client in a single network message

cursor.close() 	 ||    cursor.isClosed()	||     cursor.forEach()    ||     cursor.hasNext()	   ||     cursor.skip()

cursor.min() => inclusive lower index    || cursor.map() => iterate using an function like in JS

cursor.pretty() => used to display the results in an easy-to-read manner.

