////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
db.collection.insertOne(document, options): Inserts a single document.
db.collection.insertMany(documents, options): Inserts multiple documents.
db.collection.find(query, projection): Performs a query and returns a cursor.
db.collection.findOne(query, projection): Performs a query and returns a single document.
db.collection.updateOne(filter, update, options): Modifies a single document.
db.collection.updateMany(filter, update, options): Modifies multiple documents.
db.collection.replaceOne(filter, replacement, options): Replaces a single document.
db.collection.deleteOne(filter, options): Deletes a single document.
db.collection.deleteMany(filter, options): Deletes multiple documents.
db.collection.bulkWrite(operations, options): Provides bulk write operation functionality (mix of insert, update, delete).
db.collection.distinct(field, query, options): Returns an array of distinct values for a field.
db.collection.explain(verbosity): Returns information on query execution.
db.collection.findAndModify(options): Atomically modifies and returns a single document.
db.collection.findOneAndDelete(filter, options): Finds a single document and deletes it.
db.collection.findOneAndReplace(filter, replacement, options): Finds a single document and replaces it.
db.collection.findOneAndUpdate(filter, update, options): Finds a single document and updates it.
db.collection.mapReduce(map, reduce, options): Performs map-reduce style data aggregation.
cursor.batchSize(size): Sets the number of documents to return in each batch.
cursor.comment(comment): Adds a comment to the query.
cursor.count(applySkipLimit): Computes the number of documents in the cursor.
cursor.explain(verbosity): Returns information on the query plan for the cursor.
cursor.forEach(function): Iterates over the documents in the cursor.
cursor.hasNext(): Checks if the cursor has more documents.
cursor.limit(num): Constrains the size of the result set.
cursor.map(function): Applies a function to each document and collects return values in an array.
cursor.max(indexBound): Specifies an exclusive upper index bound.
cursor.min(indexBound): Specifies an inclusive lower index bound.
cursor.next(): Returns the next document in the cursor.


Query Operators =>
$month
Comparison: $eq, $gt, $gte, $in, $lt, $lte, $ne, $nin
Logical: $and, $not, $nor, $or
Element: $exists, $type
Evaluation: $expr, $jsonSchema, $mod, $regex, $text, $where
Geospatial: $geoIntersects, $geoWithin, $near, $nearSphere
Array: $all, $elemMatch, $size
Update Operators:

Field Update: $currentDate, $inc, $min, $max, $mul, $rename, $set, $setOnInsert, $unset
Array Update: $addToSet, $pop, $pull, $pullAll, $push, $[<identifier>], $ (positional operator)
Bitwise: $bit
Projection Operators:

$elemMatch, $meta, $project, $slice
Aggregation Pipeline Stages:

$addFields, $bucket, $bucketAuto, $collStats, $count, $facet, $geoNear,
$graphLookup, $group, $indexStats, $limit, $lookup, $match, $out, $project, 
$redact, $replaceRoot, $replaceWith, $sample, $set, $skip, $sort, $sortByCount, 

$add | $subtract | $multiply | $divide | $mod | $abs | $ceil | $floor | $exp 
| $ln | $log | $log10 | $pow | $round | $sqrt | $trunc | $rand | $inc | $mul
